{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771424410,"nonce":"iKK09t95m12IHDNT9iIIKo5ZToY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87r69sg","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/227","origin":"github"},"title":"draft PR workflow: post actual plan instead of unfilled template","message":"## Problem\n\n`worktree_create.sh --draft-pr` currently:\n\n1. Commits an unfilled template file (PLAN_ISSUE-N.md) with placeholder text\n2. Creates a draft PR with a generic \"Work in Progress\" body\n3. Posts the unfilled template as a PR comment\n\nBy the time a worktree is created, the agent has already written and gotten approval for a plan. The script should use that actual plan content.\n\n## Design\n\n### Core principle\n\nEvery approved plan gets posted as a PR comment, whether it is the initial plan or a follow-up addressing review comments. This creates a clear audit trail.\n\n### Workflow\n\n**New work:**\n\n1. User asks agent to work on an issue\n2. Agent reads the issue, explores codebase, writes a plan (plan mode)\n3. User approves the plan\n4. Agent runs `worktree_create.sh --issue N --plan-file /path/to/plan.md ...`\n5. Script creates worktree and draft PR (structured summary as body, full plan as comment)\n\n**Addressing review comments:**\n\n1. Agent reads review comments, makes a plan\n2. User approves\n3. Agent posts plan as a new PR comment (via gh pr comment directly)\n4. Agent implements changes\n\n**Resuming work:**\n\n- PR and plan already exist\n- Agent creates/enters worktree; script detects existing PR and skips creation\n\n### Changes to worktree_create.sh\n\n- Replace `--draft-pr` with `--plan-file \u003cpath\u003e` (providing a plan file implies draft PR creation)\n- When `--plan-file` is provided:\n  - Create worktree (as today)\n  - Push branch (empty commit if needed, no template file committed)\n  - Create draft PR with structured summary as body\n  - Post full plan as PR comment\n- When `--plan-file` is not provided:\n  - Create worktree only (resume case, PR already exists)\n- If a PR already exists for the branch, skip PR creation regardless\n\n### PR body format\n\nConcise, reviewer-friendly summary:\n\n```text\n## Summary\n\n\u003cBrief description — what is changing and why\u003e\n\nCloses \u003cissue-ref\u003e\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `\u003cagent name\u003e`\n**Model**: `\u003cagent model\u003e`\n```\n\n### PR comment\n\nThe approved plan, posted as-is.\n\n### Workspace vs. project repo considerations\n\nFor **workspace worktrees**, the PR targets the workspace repo. Straightforward.\n\nFor **layer worktrees**, the PR targets each project repo (one per package in `--packages`). This means:\n\n- Issue references must use cross-repo format when the issue lives in a different repo (e.g., `rolker/ros2_agent_workspace#N` in a project repo PR). The existing ISSUE_REF logic handles this.\n- When multiple packages are specified, the plan is posted as a comment on each project repo PR.\n- The PR body summary should be self-contained for the target repo. Avoid workspace-specific jargon (layer names, worktree structure) that would confuse external reviewers.\n\n### ISSUE_PLAN.md template\n\nThe template is no longer used by the script at PR creation time. It shifts roles:\n\n- **Claude Code**: does not reference the template during plan mode. Plans stay organic — plan mode already produces well-structured output without scaffolding.\n- **Other frameworks** (Copilot, Gemini CLI, etc.): the template remains as a reference for frameworks without built-in plan mode. Agents can read it and fill it out to produce their plan file.\n- Clean up the template to be human/agent-readable guidance rather than machine-fillable placeholder markup.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}